            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Kew Jay 3d /61 ¶ Dear Dr Mueller ¶  ¶ I herewith introduce to you my very particular friend Dr Hector, the very able Geologist who accompanied Capt Palliser across the Rocky mountains. ¶  He is a very...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">61.01.03</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS black-edged<seg style="font-weight: bold; ">.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Kew Jay 3d /61</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Dr Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I herewith introduce to you my very particular friend Dr Hector, the very able Geologist who accompanied Capt Palliser across the Rocky mountains.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hector accompanied the Irish explorer John Palliser on a three-year expedition through western Canada,1857-60, the chief aim of which was to find a route through the Rocky Mountains to the Pacific Ocean. </p>
               </note> He is a very fair Botanist &amp; a highly accomplished man. I beg to recommend him most cordially to you</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Most trul Yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>JD Hooker</p>
         </div>
      </body>
